<taxonomicName authority="Oliveira &amp; Soares &amp; Schultz, 2010" authorityName="Oliveira &amp; Soares &amp; Schultz" authorityYear="2010" box="[312,673,962,987]" class="Reptilia" family="Eucynodontia incertae sedis" genus="Trucidocynodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Therapsida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riograndensis" status="sp. nov.">Trucidocynodon riograndensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[680,771,962,988]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1037,1324]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[151,275,1037,1062]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin, “ 
<emphasis box="[490,574,1037,1062]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">trucido</emphasis>
” meaning “to kill cruelly”, regarding to its conspicuous specializations to carnivory; “cynodon” refers to the clade 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Owen" authorityYear="1861" box="[629,770,1074,1100]" class="Reptilia" family="Cynodontia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Therapsida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Cynodontia</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1037,1324]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[198,453,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Distribution and Age.</emphasis>
Sequence Santa Maria 2 (upper half of Santa Maria Formation), from Rhynchosaur Cenozone (
<emphasis box="[289,354,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schultz, C. L. &amp; Scherer, C. M. S. &amp; Barberena, M. C." box="[366,603,1149,1175]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="495 - 498" refId="ref31506" refString="Schultz, C. L., Scherer, C. M. S. &amp; Barberena, M. C. (2000) Bioestratigraphy of the Southern Brazilian Middle-Upper Triassic. Revista Brasileira de Geociencias, 30, 495 - 498." type="journal article" year="2000">
Schultz 
<emphasis box="[465,520,1149,1174]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
), in a stratigraphic level with great abundance of the traversodontid 
<taxonomicName box="[151,471,1186,1211]" class="Reptilia" family="Traversodontidae" genus="Exaeretodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Therapsida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riograndensis">
<emphasis box="[151,471,1186,1211]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Exaeretodon riograndensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Carnian in age (by the presence of hyperodapedontid rhynchosaurs); the fossiliferous outcrop is named “Sítio Janner” (coordinates 
<geoCoordinate box="[758,898,1224,1250]" degrees="29" direction="south" minutes="40" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" precision="15" seconds="45" value="-29.679167">29°40’45”S</geoCoordinate>
/ 
<geoCoordinate box="[908,1058,1224,1250]" degrees="53" direction="west" minutes="17" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" precision="15" seconds="34" value="-53.292778">53°17’34”W</geoCoordinate>
), Agudo Municipality (approximately 
<quantity box="[238,326,1261,1287]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="km" value="200.0">200 km</quantity>
east from Porto Alegre), 
<collectingRegion box="[626,913,1261,1287]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName authority="Grande" authorityName="Grande" box="[626,761,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Rio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rio Grande</taxonomicName>
do Sul State
</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[925,996,1261,1287]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1012,1084,1261,1287]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,255,1493,1517]" captionTargetBox="[171,1403,192,1463]" captionTargetId="figure-227@6.[151,1436,173,1469]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Geographical location of study area. A, Rio Grande do Sul State (Zerfass et al. 2003). B, road map with City of Agudo pointed. C, stratigraphic section of Sítio Janner outcrop." pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1037,1324]" box="[198,1001,1298,1324]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[198,420,1298,1323]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Generic diagnosis.</emphasis>
As for the species, by the monotipy of the genus.
</paragraph>
