<caption pageId="6" pageNumber="7" startId="6.[151,255,1493,1517]" targetBox="[171,1403,192,1463]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1493,1548]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1493,1517]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Geographical location of study area. A, 
<taxonomicName authority="Grande" authorityName="Grande" box="[710,834,1493,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Rio" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Rio Grande</taxonomicName>
do Sul State (
<bibRefCitation author="Zerfass, H. &amp; Lavina, E. L. &amp; Schultz, C. L. &amp; Garcia, A. J. V. &amp; Faccini, U. F. &amp; Chemale, F., Jr." box="[980,1183,1493,1516]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="85 - 105" refId="ref32209" refString="Zerfass, H., Lavina, E. L., Schultz, C. L., Garcia, A. J. V., Faccini, U. F. &amp; Chemale, F., Jr. (2003) Sequence stratigraphy of continental Triassic strata of Southernmost Brazil: a contribution to Southwestern Gondwana palaeogeography and palaeoclimate. Sedimentary Geology, 161, 85 - 105." type="journal article" year="2003">
Zerfass 
